						<summary>

						<p>On the second pillar in the same cave.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅgachōḷadēva I: Year 40 = 1109-10 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Pugaḻmādu viḷaṅga,</hi> etc.</p>						

						<p>It records that Vīraśēkharan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Virudarājabhayaṁkara Adalaiyūrnāḍāḻvān granted a remission of taxes on all the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> lands situated in a number of his villages irrigated by the river Tēnāṟu, including Tirukkuṉṟakkuḍi, Vēlavūr and Śāḻi. </p>						

						</summary>
